law.text:
As used in KRS 64.5277 to 64.5279:
"City" means:
Any city of any class;
An urban-county government that does not participate in the county officers training program under KRS 64.5275; and
A consolidated local government that does not participate in the county officers training program under KRS 64.5275;
"City officer" means:
Any individual elected to a city office existing under KRS Chapter 83A;
Any individual elected to a city office existing under KRS Chapter 67A or 67C, if the respective government does not participate in the county officers training program under KRS 64.5275;
Any individual appointed to fill a vacancy in an elected city office as defined under paragraph (a) or (b) of this subsection; and
Any individual serving in a nonelected city office as defined by KRS 83A.080 that is designated by the city as eligible for participation in the city officers training program in the ordinance adopted pursuant to KRS 64.5278;
"Training incentive multiplier" means a number of one (1) to four (4) that is used to calculate the final training incentive to be paid to a city officer eligible to participate in the training incentive program; and
"Training unit" means fifteen (15) clock hours of attendance or participation in qualifying courses during a calendar year.
